  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Trading Analyst",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong><br /><br />Provide market analytic support to the trading and refinery team by delivering timely insights, data-driven recommendations, and performance analysis. Enhance trading effectiveness through research, quantitative modeling, and operational support to enable strategic and profitable decision making.<br /></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Conduct market research and maintain analytical models to support crude trading decisions.</li><li>Build and enhance quantitative models for forecasting prices, flows, arbitrage, and supply–demand dynamics.</li><li>Analyze large datasets (pricing, fundamentals, freight, refinery yields) to identify trading signals and optimization opportunities.</li><li>Prepare daily/weekly/monthly market reports, pricing updates, and actionable insights for traders.</li><li>Track trading positions, exposure, and P&L; ensure accuracy of valuations and trade data.</li><li>Maintain and automate datasets, dashboards, and analytics tools to improve decision quality and workflow efficiency.</li><li>Perform scenario analysis, risk metrics assessment, and back-testing of trading strategies.</li><li>Collaborate with Operations, Risk, Finance, and Supply teams to support seamless execution and reporting.</li><li>Provide analytical input to value chain strategy and optimization and broader commercial strategy evaluations.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Engineering, Science, Economics, Finance, Data Science, or a related discipline.</li><li>1–3 years in trading analytics, market analysis, commodities, energy, finance, refinery supply & commercial business or a similar analytical role.</li><li>Analytical Skills, Quantitative Modeling, Market Analysis, Data Management, Risk Management, Problem Solving, Communication, Collaboration, Technical Proficiency (Excel / Python / SQL).</li><li>TOEIC Score: 600</li></ul>",
